comments.body:
This patch will always return true because `confirmed_by_node` is statically false, so it will be an endless loop of new connections.
```
     if (!confirmed_by_node) {
-        return;
+        return true;
     }
```

What I suggest is tracking confirmed by node id, and set it to true if we receive the PONG or if we timeout after we already sent an INV. Then here check if the confirmed by node id is false, and if so call `NumToOpenAdd(1)`. Remove all other `NumToOpenAdd(1)` calls.

Right now we pass confirmed by node id statically as true only when we receive a PONG, and false always when we finalize the node. Instead, track the confirmed by node status and use it in FinishBroadcast only here at FinalizeNode.

